This page demonstrates the <code>neowiki_value</code> parser function for reading individual property values from Subjects.

== Reading from the Current Page's Subject ==

When used on a page with a Subject, <code>neowiki_value</code> reads from that page's main Subject by default.
Visit [[ACME Inc]] to see these values in the infobox.

{| class="wikitable"
! Property !! Syntax !! Result
|-
| Founded at || <code><nowiki>{{#neowiki_value: Founded at | page=ACME Inc}}</nowiki></code> || {{#neowiki_value: Founded at | page=ACME Inc}}
|-
| Websites || <code><nowiki>{{#neowiki_value: Websites | page=ACME Inc}}</nowiki></code> || {{#neowiki_value: Websites | page=ACME Inc}}
|-
| Products || <code><nowiki>{{#neowiki_value: Products | page=ACME Inc}}</nowiki></code> || {{#neowiki_value: Products | page=ACME Inc}}
|-
| World domination progress || <code><nowiki>{{#neowiki_value: World domination progress | page=ACME Inc}}</nowiki></code> || {{#neowiki_value: World domination progress | page=ACME Inc}}%
|-
| Missing property || <code><nowiki>{{#neowiki_value: Nonexistent | page=ACME Inc}}</nowiki></code> || (empty) {{#neowiki_value: Nonexistent | page=ACME Inc}}
|}

== Custom Separator ==

Multi-valued properties use <code>, </code> as separator by default. Use <code>separator=</code> to change it:

* Default: {{#neowiki_value: Products | page=ACME Inc}}
* Semicolons: {{#neowiki_value: Products | page=ACME Inc | separator=;}}
* Pipe: {{#neowiki_value: Products | page=ACME Inc | separator={{!}}}}

== Cross-Page Lookups ==

Read values from any page using the <code>page=</code> parameter:

* Professional Wiki was founded at: {{#neowiki_value: Founded at | page=Professional Wiki}}
* ACME Inc was founded at: {{#neowiki_value: Founded at | page=ACME Inc}}

== Inline Usage ==

The parser function can be used inline in running text:

{{#neowiki_value: Products | page=Professional Wiki}} are products of Professional Wiki, which was founded in {{#neowiki_value: Founded at | page=Professional Wiki}}.
